Package io.github.ai4ci.output

package io.github.ai4ci.output
Data export and output generation for simulation results and analytics.

This package provides comprehensive data export capabilities for capturing simulation results at different stages of the execution lifecycle. The exports are organized by Export.Stage to ensure data is captured at appropriate points during simulation execution.

Export Stage Organization

Exports are triggered at specific stages of the simulation lifecycle:

BASELINE Stage

Exports that occur once during model initialization, capturing baseline configuration and static model characteristics:

  • InfectivityProfileCSV - Baseline infectivity profiles exported to ip.csv

START Stage

Exports that occur at simulation startup, capturing initial state and configuration parameters:

  • DebugParametersCSV - Debug and configuration parameters exported to debug.csv
  • PersonDemographicsCSV - Initial demographic data exported to demog.duckdb

UPDATE Stage

Exports that occur during each time step update, capturing dynamic simulation state and epidemiological metrics:

  • OutbreakCSV - Summary statistics exported to summary.csv
  • OutbreakHistoryCSV - Test positivity time series exported to test-positivity.csv
  • OutbreakContactCountCSV - Contact network statistics exported to contact-counts.csv
  • OutbreakBehaviourCountCSV - Behavior state counts exported to behaviours.csv
  • LineListCSV - Case line list data exported to linelist.duckdb
  • PersonTestsCSV - Individual test results exported to cases.duckdb
  • ContactCSV - Contact tracing data exported to contacts.duckdb

FINISH Stage

Exports that occur at simulation completion, capturing final state and summary results:

  • OutbreakFinalStateCSV - Final simulation state exported to final-state.csv

Output Formats

The package supports multiple output formats:

  • CSV files: Standard comma-separated values for interoperability
  • DuckDB databases: High-performance columnar storage for large datasets

Writer Implementations

Different writer implementations handle the output generation:

  • CSVWriter - Writes to CSV files
  • DuckDBWriter - Writes to DuckDB databases

Data Mapping

The CSVMapper class provides mapping utilities to convert internal model objects to export-friendly CSV representations.

Common Base Interfaces

Common base interfaces ensure consistency across export types:

  • CommonCSV.State - Base for state-related exports
  • OutputWriter.Writeable - Marker interface for exportable data

Integration with Flow Package

The output package integrates with the flow execution framework through:

  • Export annotations that declare export timing and parameters
  • Export.Selector interfaces that extract data from models
  • Automatic invocation by SimulationExporter during execution
